  "slug": "vegan-carrot-cake",
  "title": "Vegan carrot cake",
  "subtitle": "Moist, spiced loaf with a lemon drizzle",
  "excerpt": "A vegan carrot cake made with flaxseed egg and vegetable oil that is just as moist as the dairy original. Cinnamon, ginger, and walnuts throughout; lemon drizzle on top.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Carrot cake as a concept spans many traditions, from medieval European spiced fruit cakes through to the American cream-cheese frosted version that became ubiquitous after the 1960s. This vegan adaptation replaces eggs with flaxseed and dairy with plant milk, following techniques developed in Isa Chandra Moskowitz's Veganomicon (2007) and Meera Sodha's East (2019).",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Oil-based cakes stay moist longer than butter-based ones, which is one reason a vegan carrot cake can be just as good as the original. The flaxseed egg gels in water and binds the batter without affecting the flavour. Grate the carrot coarsely; fine gratings disappear into the crumb and lose their texture.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "tip"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Squeeze excess moisture from the grated carrot in a clean tea towel before weighing it out. Too much water in the batter can prevent the cake setting in the centre.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
